\u0026amp;w=2400 2400w\" src=\"https://platform.polygon.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2025/07/Screenshot-2025-07-03-132039.png?quality=90\u0026amp;strip=all\u0026amp;crop=0%2C0%2C100%2C100\u0026amp;w=2400\"/\u003e\u003c/a\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\u003c/div\u003e\u003cp\u003e\u003ccite\u003eImage: Black Wings Game Studio/Sega via Polygon\u003c/cite\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\u003c/div\u003e\u003cp\u003eYou can unlock Yaoling’s Synergy Bond by completing the “Foreign Exchange” side mission. Increasing Yaoling’s bond provides cooking and crafting upgrades for use in and out of battle.\u003c/p\u003e\u003cp\u003eYaoling is an outgoing and carefree person who has some childish tendencies. She’s a first-year university student from Sichuan, China, studying abroad in Japan. Yaoling is trying to find herself while abroad, but isn’t quite sure of where life will take her.\u003c/p\u003e\u003cdiv\u003e\u003cp id=\"tomoko-noge-moko\"\u003e\u003ch3\u003eTomoko Noge (Moko)\u003c/h3\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\u003c/div\u003e\u003cdiv\u003e\u003cp\u003e\u003ca href=\"https://platform.polygon.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2025/07/Screenshot-2025-07-03-132054.png?quality=90\u0026amp;strip=all\u0026amp;crop=0,0,100,100\" data-pswp-height=\"1440\" data-pswp-width=\"2560\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer\"\u003e\u003cimg alt=\"A screenshot of Tomoko in Persona 5 The Phantom X on PC.\" data-chromatic=\"ignore\" loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" data-nimg=\"fill\" sizes=\"(max-width: 639px) 100vw, (max-width: 1023px) 50vw, 700px\" srcset=\"https://platform.polygon.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2025/07/Screenshot-2025-07-03-132054.png?quality=90\u0026amp;strip=all\u0026amp;crop=0%2C0%2C100%2C100\u0026amp;w=256 256w, https://platform.polygon.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2025/07/Screenshot-2025-07-03-132054.png?quality=90\u0026amp;strip=all\u0026amp;crop=0%2C0%2C100%2C100\u0026amp;w=376 376w, https://platform.polygon.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2025/07/Screenshot-2025-07-03-132054.png?quality=90\u0