=all\u0026amp;crop=0%2C0%2C100%2C100\u0026amp;w=2048 2048w, https://platform.polygon.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2025/07/Screenshot-2025-07-03-132054.png?quality=90\u0026amp;strip=all\u0026amp;crop=0%2C0%2C100%2C100\u0026amp;w=2400 2400w\" src=\"https://platform.polygon.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2025/07/Screenshot-2025-07-03-132054.png?quality=90\u0026amp;strip=all\u0026amp;crop=0%2C0%2C100%2C100\u0026amp;w=2400\"/\u003e\u003c/a\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\u003c/div\u003e\u003cp\u003eTomoko’s Synergy Bond is unlocked by completing the “Part-Time Dreamer” side mission. Increasing Tomoko’s bond provides part-time job upgrades, such as a boost to your social stats.\u003c/p\u003e\u003cp\u003eTomoko is a second-year student at Kokatsu Academy and is one of the first NPCs you meet in \u003cem\u003eThe Phantom X\u003c/em\u003e. She tries to deny her feelings for the protagonist, but it’s pretty obvious how she feels. Tomoko wants to gain experience in life and decides to take on multiple part-time jobs to achieve this goal.\u003c/p\u003e\u003cdiv\u003e\u003cp id=\"other-synergy-bonds-in-persona-5-the-phantom-x\"\u003e\u003ch2\u003eOther Synergy Bonds in Persona 5: The Phantom X\u003c/h2\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\u003c/div\u003e\u003cp\u003eThe characters below are not romanceable, but you can still spend your time with them to earn some good perks.\u003c/p\u003e\u003cdiv\u003e\u003cp id=\"lufel-cattle\"\u003e\u003ch3\u003eLufel (Cattle)\u003c/h3\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\u003c/div\u003e\u003cdiv\u003e\u003cdiv\u003e\u003cp\u003e\u003ca href=\"https://platform.polygon.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2025/07/Screenshot-2025-07-03-105258.png?quality=90\u0026amp;strip=all\u0026amp;crop=0,0,100,100\" data-pswp-height=\"2160\" data-pswp-width=\"3840\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer\"\u003e\u003cimg alt=\"A screenshot of the Synergy screen in Persona 5 The Phantom X on Steam\" data-chromatic=\"ignore\" loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" data-nimg=\"fill\" sizes=\"(max-width: 639px) 100vw